  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Utility for password generation on LliureX</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command> 
      <arg choice="opt">options</arg>
      <arg choice="plain">name</arg>
      <group choice="req">
         <arg>show</arg>
         <arg>gen</arg>
         <arg>remove</arg>
      </group>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>This manual page documents briefly the
      <command>&dhpackage;</command> command.</para>

    <para><command>&dhpackage;</command> is a command line utility to create passwords.</para>
    <para>These passwords are stored in /etc/lliurex-secrets/passgen/ directory.</para>

    <para>This manual page was written for the &debian; distribution
      because the original program does not have a manual page.</para>
      
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    <para>A summary of options is included below.</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-l, --length=PASSLENGTH</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Set the password length of characters generated. By default 12</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-o, --owner=OWNER</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Set the owner of the password file generated. By default root</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-g, --group=GROUP</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Set the group of the password file generated. By default root</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-m, --mode=MODE</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Set the permission in octal of the password generated. By default 600</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
    	<term><option>--force, --chucknorris</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Force mode. the operation is made, although it can be unsure or dangeorus</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>COMMANDS</title>
    <para>A summary of commands is included below.</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>show</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Display the password</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>gen</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Generate the password</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>remove</option></term>
        <listitem><para>Remove the password</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>BUGS</title>

    <para>Create a new ticket in the LliureX Project Manager by introducing
      your email and a brief explanation of the trouble.</para>
    <para>&dhticket;</para>

